    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Oil Pan and Oil Pickup Tube - Removal - Oil Pickup Tube</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26506.1.3" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Oil Pickup Tube</title>
        <figure id="e3000704" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the oil pickup tube (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">CF - Remove two oil pickup tube mounting bolts (M6 x 20) and oil pickup tube.</para>
            <para>Stripped chassis - Remove three oil pickup tube mounting bolts (M6 x 25 - patch type) and oil pickup
                tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3000705" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the pickup tube O-ring (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the oil pickup tube O-ring.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
